{
  "stem": "5470.5",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I drove further up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there, I saw the first Canadian killed on the left-hand side of the road.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Further into the township past the, uh, milk, uh, cooperative, by the hotel, so second one.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's where I met another friend of the underground movement.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from there on, we started off talking about what we were going to do after the liberation.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I, uh, made known to them that I didn't want to have a Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What I said-- that, uh, we were going to be as soon as the Germans were leaving, then we were under control of the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No Red Cross, because I know what the Germans are doing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they don't respect the Red Cross at all.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I said, I'm going to put on the, uh, [? bright ?] place, [? appelplatz. ?] And a cloth of, um-- Jewish stars, yellow stars, which were printed on it on the, uh, [? bright ?] place.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That if then, they can see that we are, anyhow, a Jewish camp.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that's what happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The day thereafter, the Germans left on the 11th and by six o'clock, half past six that evening.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's where they start shooting.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The whole day, they were sitting outside doing nothing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was beautiful day, sunny.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, uh-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I had to go in-- into the camp again, because by that time, we were living outside camp, to my office.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I had my office just facing his office.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So I could see-- see through the window what they were doing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, um-- as soon as I was inside the camp, I got the order, 'don't get out anymore.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
